http://purl.org/dc/terms/description.value: Forensics II is a two-semester course which will provide students with an opportunity to demonstrate communication skills at an intermediate level. Students will cultivate effective vocal delivery, emphasizing articulation, projection, and inflection. They will cultivate appropriate movement and gesture to accentuate meaning. These communication skills, which will serve students well throughout their lives, will be embedded throughout the course. Students will acquire skills necessary to make aesthetic choices in the selection, preparation, and presentation of literature from a wide variety of genres. Students will practice persuasive techniques in both extemporaneous and prepared formats.
